1. semantics only pertains to a phrase, not words
2. causal score not distinctive from correlation score: 
they should be different!
3. causal scores not comparable among different pairs hence not appropriate 
to sum up together to get total score
4. an event typically involves a subject, a predicate and an object; 
the importance of these components are different. maybe possible to calculate
their relative importance to give them different amount of boosting.
5. Pronoun in the response sometimes can be eliminated together with the 
referred entity in the question.
6. did we handle negations in the original data. better do it...
